Note:
Runa Standard Library: Secrets Management Module

Provides comprehensive secrets management capabilities including secure storage,
encryption, access control, rotation, and audit logging. This module is designed
for production environments requiring enterprise-grade security for sensitive
configuration data such as API keys, passwords, certificates, and tokens.

Features:
- Secure secret storage with multiple backend support
- Strong encryption using industry-standard algorithms (AES-256-GCM, ChaCha20-Poly1305)
- Secret versioning and rotation capabilities
- Fine-grained access control and permission management
- Comprehensive audit logging and monitoring
- Secret lifecycle management (creation, rotation, expiration, deletion)
- Integration with external secret management systems (HashiCorp Vault, AWS Secrets Manager, etc.)
- Secure secret sharing and temporary access tokens
- Secret injection into application configuration
- Compliance with security standards (SOC 2, FIPS 140-2, Common Criteria)

Security Features:
- Zero-knowledge encryption architecture
- Secure key derivation using PBKDF2, Argon2, or scrypt
- Perfect forward secrecy for secret communications
- Secure memory handling and cleanup
- Side-channel attack resistance
- Tamper detection and integrity verification
- Secure random number generation
- Protection against timing attacks

Backend Support:
- File-based encrypted storage
- In-memory secure storage
- Database-backed storage with encryption
- Cloud KMS integration (AWS KMS, Azure Key Vault, Google Cloud KMS)
- Hardware Security Module (HSM) support
- Distributed secret sharing (Shamir's Secret Sharing)

Thread Safety: All secret operations are thread-safe and designed
for high-concurrency environments with minimal performance impact.
:End Note

Import "stdlib/config/environment" as environment
Import "stdlib/os/os" as os

Note: Core Secret Types and Structures
Type SecretType is:
    | API_KEY
    | PASSWORD
    | TOKEN
    | CERTIFICATE
    | PRIVATE_KEY
    | DATABASE_CREDENTIAL
    | OAUTH_SECRET
    | ENCRYPTION_KEY
    | SIGNING_KEY
    | WEBHOOK_SECRET
    | SERVICE_ACCOUNT_KEY
    | TLS_CERTIFICATE
    | SSH_KEY
    | CUSTOM

Type called "SecretMetadata":
    secret_id as String
    name as String
    secret_type as SecretType
    description as Optional[String] defaults to None
    tags as List[String] defaults to list containing
    created_by as String
    created_at as Float
    last_accessed as Optional[Float] defaults to None
    last_modified as Float
    access_count as Integer defaults to 0
    version as Integer defaults to 1
    expires_at as Optional[Float] defaults to None
    rotation_interval as Optional[Float] defaults to None
    last_rotation as Optional[Float] defaults to None
    compliance_level as String defaults to "standard"
    audit_enabled as Boolean defaults to true
    metadata as Dictionary[String, Any] defaults to dictionary containing

Type called "Secret":
    metadata as SecretMetadata
    encrypted_value as String
    encryption_algorithm as String
    key_id as String
    iv as String
    auth_tag as Optional[String] defaults to None
    compressed as Boolean defaults to false
    encoding as String defaults to "base64"
    checksum as String
    size as Integer
    secret_metadata as Dictionary[String, Any] defaults to dictionary containing

Type called "SecretStore":
    store_id as String
    store_type as String
    store_config as Dictionary[String, Any] defaults to dictionary containing
    encryption_enabled as Boolean defaults to true
    master_key_id as Optional[String] defaults to None
    access_policy as Dictionary[String, Any] defaults to dictionary containing
    audit_config as Dictionary[String, Any] defaults to dictionary containing
    performance_metrics as Dictionary[String, Any] defaults to dictionary containing
    created_at as Float
    last_health_check as Optional[Float] defaults to None
    metadata as Dictionary[String, Any] defaults to dictionary containing

Type called "SecretAccess":
    access_id as String
    secret_id as String
    principal as String
    permissions as List[String] defaults to list containing
    granted_by as String
    granted_at as Float
    expires_at as Optional[Float] defaults to None
    conditions as Dictionary[String, Any] defaults to dictionary containing
    audit_trail as List[Dictionary[String, Any]] defaults to list containing
    metadata as Dictionary[String, Any] defaults to dictionary containing

Type SecretResult[T] is:
    | SecretSuccess with value as T and audit_info as Dictionary[String, Any]
    | SecretNotFound with secret_id as String and reason as String
    | SecretAccessDenied with secret_id as String and principal as String and required_permission as String
    | SecretExpired with secret_id as String and expired_at as Float
    | SecretCorrupted with secret_id as String and error_details as String
    | SecretException with error_message as String and error_code as String

Type called "EncryptionConfig":
    algorithm as String defaults to "AES-256-GCM"
    key_derivation as String defaults to "PBKDF2"
    iterations as Integer defaults to 100000
    salt_size as Integer defaults to 32
    iv_size as Integer defaults to 12
    tag_size as Integer defaults to 16
    compression_enabled as Boolean defaults to false
    encoding as String defaults to "base64"
    metadata as Dictionary[String, Any] defaults to dictionary containing

Type called "AuditEvent":
    event_id as String
    event_type as String
    secret_id as Optional[String] defaults to None
    principal as String
    timestamp as Float
    source_ip as Optional[String] defaults to None
    user_agent as Optional[String] defaults to None
    operation as String
    success as Boolean
    error_message as Optional[String] defaults to None
    resource_accessed as Optional[String] defaults to None
    additional_data as Dictionary[String, Any] defaults to dictionary containing
:End Note

Note: Core Secret Management Operations
Process called "create_secret" that takes name as String and value as String and secret_type as SecretType and metadata as Optional[Dictionary[String, Any]] and store as Optional[SecretStore] returns SecretResult[String]:
    Let current_time be get_current_timestamp
    Let secret_id be generate_secret_id
    Let final_metadata be metadata if metadata is not None else dictionary containing
    Let final_store be store if store is not None else get_default_secret_store
    
    Try:
        Note: Validate secret creation permissions
        Let permission_check be check_secret_permission with:
            principal as get_current_principal
            operation as "create"
            resource as name
            store as final_store
        
        If not permission_check.allowed:
            Return SecretAccessDenied with:
                secret_id as secret_id
                principal as get_current_principal
                required_permission as "create"
        
        Note: Validate secret value
        Let validation_result be validate_secret_value with:
            value as value
            secret_type as secret_type
        
        If not validation_result.valid:
            Return SecretException with:
                error_message as "Secret validation failed: " plus validation_result.error_message
                error_code as "VALIDATION_ERROR"
        
        Note: Encrypt secret value
        Let encryption_result be encrypt_secret_value with:
            value as value
            config as final_store.store_config
            store as final_store
        
        If not encryption_result.success:
            Return SecretException with:
                error_message as "Secret encryption failed: " plus encryption_result.error_message
                error_code as "ENCRYPTION_ERROR"
        
        Note: Create secret metadata
        Let secret_metadata be SecretMetadata with:
            secret_id as secret_id
            name as name
            secret_type as secret_type
            description as get_safe_value with dict as final_metadata and key as "description" and default as None
            tags as get_safe_value with dict as final_metadata and key as "tags" and default as list containing
            created_by as get_current_principal
            created_at as current_time
            last_accessed as None
            last_modified as current_time
            access_count as 0
            version as 1
            expires_at as get_safe_value with dict as final_metadata and key as "expires_at" and default as None
            rotation_interval as get_safe_value with dict as final_metadata and key as "rotation_interval" and default as None
            last_rotation as None
            compliance_level as get_safe_value with dict as final_metadata and key as "compliance_level" and default as "standard"
            audit_enabled as get_safe_value with dict as final_metadata and key as "audit_enabled" and default as true
            metadata as final_metadata
        
        Note: Create secret object
        Let secret be Secret with:
            metadata as secret_metadata
            encrypted_value as encryption_result.encrypted_data
            encryption_algorithm as encryption_result.algorithm
            key_id as encryption_result.key_id
            iv as encryption_result.iv
            auth_tag as encryption_result.auth_tag
            compressed as encryption_result.compressed
            encoding as encryption_result.encoding
            checksum as encryption_result.checksum
            size as length of value
            secret_metadata as dictionary containing
        
        Note: Store secret
        Let store_result be store_secret_in_backend with:
            secret as secret
            store as final_store
        
        If not store_result.success:
            Return SecretException with:
                error_message as "Secret storage failed: " plus store_result.error_message
                error_code as "STORAGE_ERROR"
        
        Note: Log audit event
        If secret_metadata.audit_enabled:
            log_audit_event with:
                event_type as "SECRET_CREATED"
                secret_id as secret_id
                principal as get_current_principal
                operation as "create"
                success as true
                additional_data as dictionary containing:
                    "secret_name" as name
                    "secret_type" as secret_type as String
                    "store_id" as final_store.store_id
        
        Return SecretSuccess with:
            value as secret_id
            audit_info as dictionary containing:
                "operation" as "create"
                "secret_id" as secret_id
                "timestamp" as current_time
    
    Catch error:
        Note: Log failed creation
        log_audit_event with:
            event_type as "SECRET_CREATION_FAILED"
            secret_id as secret_id
            principal as get_current_principal
            operation as "create"
            success as false
            additional_data as dictionary containing "error" as error.message
        
        Return SecretException with:
            error_message as "Secret creation exception: " plus error.message
            error_code as "CREATION_EXCEPTION"

Process called "get_secret" that takes secret_id as String and store as Optional[SecretStore] returns SecretResult[String]:
    Let current_time be get_current_timestamp
    Let final_store be store if store is not None else get_default_secret_store
    
    Try:
        Note: Validate secret access permissions
        Let permission_check be check_secret_permission with:
            principal as get_current_principal
            operation as "read"
            resource as secret_id
            store as final_store
        
        If not permission_check.allowed:
            log_audit_event with:
                event_type as "SECRET_ACCESS_DENIED"
                secret_id as secret_id
                principal as get_current_principal
                operation as "read"
                success as false
                additional_data as dictionary containing "reason" as "insufficient_permissions"
            
            Return SecretAccessDenied with:
                secret_id as secret_id
                principal as get_current_principal
                required_permission as "read"
        
        Note: Retrieve secret from store
        Let retrieve_result be retrieve_secret_from_backend with:
            secret_id as secret_id
            store as final_store
        
        If not retrieve_result.found:
            log_audit_event with:
                event_type as "SECRET_NOT_FOUND"
                secret_id as secret_id
                principal as get_current_principal
                operation as "read"
                success as false
                additional_data as dictionary containing
            
            Return SecretNotFound with:
                secret_id as secret_id
                reason as "Secret not found in store"
        
        Let secret be retrieve_result.secret
        
        Note: Check if secret has expired
        If secret.metadata.expires_at is not None and current_time is greater than secret.metadata.expires_at:
            log_audit_event with:
                event_type as "SECRET_EXPIRED_ACCESS"
                secret_id as secret_id
                principal as get_current_principal
                operation as "read"
                success as false
                additional_data as dictionary containing:
                    "expired_at" as secret.metadata.expires_at
                    "current_time" as current_time
            
            Return SecretExpired with:
                secret_id as secret_id
                expired_at as secret.metadata.expires_at
        
        Note: Decrypt secret value
        Let decryption_result be decrypt_secret_value with:
            encrypted_data as secret.encrypted_value
            encryption_algorithm as secret.encryption_algorithm
            key_id as secret.key_id
            iv as secret.iv
            auth_tag as secret.auth_tag
            config as final_store.store_config
            store as final_store
        
        If not decryption_result.success:
            log_audit_event with:
                event_type as "SECRET_DECRYPTION_FAILED"
                secret_id as secret_id
                principal as get_current_principal
                operation as "read"
                success as false
                additional_data as dictionary containing "error" as decryption_result.error_message
            
            Return SecretCorrupted with:
                secret_id as secret_id
                error_details as "Decryption failed: " plus decryption_result.error_message
        
        Note: Update access tracking
        Let update_result be update_secret_access_tracking with:
            secret as secret
            principal as get_current_principal
            timestamp as current_time
            store as final_store
        
        Note: Log successful access
        If secret.metadata.audit_enabled:
            log_audit_event with:
                event_type as "SECRET_ACCESSED"
                secret_id as secret_id
                principal as get_current_principal
                operation as "read"
                success as true
                additional_data as dictionary containing:
                    "secret_name" as secret.metadata.name
                    "access_count" as secret.metadata.access_count plus 1
        
        Return SecretSuccess with:
            value as decryption_result.decrypted_value
            audit_info as dictionary containing:
                "operation" as "read"
                "secret_id" as secret_id
                "access_time" as current_time
                "access_count" as secret.metadata.access_count plus 1
    
    Catch error:
        log_audit_event with:
            event_type as "SECRET_ACCESS_EXCEPTION"
            secret_id as secret_id
            principal as get_current_principal
            operation as "read"
            success as false
            additional_data as dictionary containing "error" as error.message
        
        Return SecretException with:
            error_message as "Secret retrieval exception: " plus error.message
            error_code as "RETRIEVAL_EXCEPTION"

Process called "update_secret" that takes secret_id as String and new_value as String and metadata as Optional[Dictionary[String, Any]] and store as Optional[SecretStore] returns SecretResult[Integer]:
    Let current_time be get_current_timestamp
    Let final_store be store if store is not None else get_default_secret_store
    Let final_metadata be metadata if metadata is not None else dictionary containing
    
    Try:
        Note: Validate update permissions
        Let permission_check be check_secret_permission with:
            principal as get_current_principal
            operation as "update"
            resource as secret_id
            store as final_store
        
        If not permission_check.allowed:
            Return SecretAccessDenied with:
                secret_id as secret_id
                principal as get_current_principal
                required_permission as "update"
        
        Note: Retrieve existing secret
        Let retrieve_result be retrieve_secret_from_backend with:
            secret_id as secret_id
            store as final_store
        
        If not retrieve_result.found:
            Return SecretNotFound with:
                secret_id as secret_id
                reason as "Cannot update non-existent secret"
        
        Let existing_secret be retrieve_result.secret
        
        Note: Validate new secret value
        Let validation_result be validate_secret_value with:
            value as new_value
            secret_type as existing_secret.metadata.secret_type
        
        If not validation_result.valid:
            Return SecretException with:
                error_message as "Secret validation failed: " plus validation_result.error_message
                error_code as "VALIDATION_ERROR"
        
        Note: Archive current version if versioning is enabled
        If final_store.store_config contains "versioning_enabled" and final_store.store_config["versioning_enabled"]:
            Let archive_result be archive_secret_version with:
                secret as existing_secret
                store as final_store
        
        Note: Encrypt new value
        Let encryption_result be encrypt_secret_value with:
            value as new_value
            config as final_store.store_config
            store as final_store
        
        If not encryption_result.success:
            Return SecretException with:
                error_message as "Secret encryption failed: " plus encryption_result.error_message
                error_code as "ENCRYPTION_ERROR"
        
        Note: Update secret metadata
        Let updated_metadata be existing_secret.metadata
        Set updated_metadata.last_modified to current_time
        Set updated_metadata.version to updated_metadata.version plus 1
        
        Note: Apply metadata updates
        If final_metadata contains "description":
            Set updated_metadata.description to final_metadata["description"]
        If final_metadata contains "tags":
            Set updated_metadata.tags to final_metadata["tags"]
        If final_metadata contains "expires_at":
            Set updated_metadata.expires_at to final_metadata["expires_at"]
        If final_metadata contains "rotation_interval":
            Set updated_metadata.rotation_interval to final_metadata["rotation_interval"]
        
        Note: Create updated secret
        Let updated_secret be Secret with:
            metadata as updated_metadata
            encrypted_value as encryption_result.encrypted_data
            encryption_algorithm as encryption_result.algorithm
            key_id as encryption_result.key_id
            iv as encryption_result.iv
            auth_tag as encryption_result.auth_tag
            compressed as encryption_result.compressed
            encoding as encryption_result.encoding
            checksum as encryption_result.checksum
            size as length of new_value
            secret_metadata as existing_secret.secret_metadata
        
        Note: Store updated secret
        Let store_result be store_secret_in_backend with:
            secret as updated_secret
            store as final_store
        
        If not store_result.success:
            Return SecretException with:
                error_message as "Secret update storage failed: " plus store_result.error_message
                error_code as "STORAGE_ERROR"
        
        Note: Log audit event
        If updated_metadata.audit_enabled:
            log_audit_event with:
                event_type as "SECRET_UPDATED"
                secret_id as secret_id
                principal as get_current_principal
                operation as "update"
                success as true
                additional_data as dictionary containing:
                    "old_version" as existing_secret.metadata.version
                    "new_version" as updated_metadata.version
                    "secret_name" as updated_metadata.name
        
        Return SecretSuccess with:
            value as updated_metadata.version
            audit_info as dictionary containing:
                "operation" as "update"
                "secret_id" as secret_id
                "new_version" as updated_metadata.version
                "timestamp" as current_time
    
    Catch error:
        log_audit_event with:
            event_type as "SECRET_UPDATE_FAILED"
            secret_id as secret_id
            principal as get_current_principal
            operation as "update"
            success as false
            additional_data as dictionary containing "error" as error.message
        
        Return SecretException with:
            error_message as "Secret update exception: " plus error.message
            error_code as "UPDATE_EXCEPTION"

Process called "delete_secret" that takes secret_id as String and force as Optional[Boolean] and store as Optional[SecretStore] returns SecretResult[Boolean]:
    Let current_time be get_current_timestamp
    Let final_force be force if force is not None else false
    Let final_store be store if store is not None else get_default_secret_store
    
    Try:
        Note: Validate delete permissions
        Let permission_check be check_secret_permission with:
            principal as get_current_principal
            operation as "delete"
            resource as secret_id
            store as final_store
        
        If not permission_check.allowed:
            Return SecretAccessDenied with:
                secret_id as secret_id
                principal as get_current_principal
                required_permission as "delete"
        
        Note: Retrieve secret for validation
        Let retrieve_result be retrieve_secret_from_backend with:
            secret_id as secret_id
            store as final_store
        
        If not retrieve_result.found:
            Return SecretNotFound with:
                secret_id as secret_id
                reason as "Cannot delete non-existent secret"
        
        Let secret be retrieve_result.secret
        
        Note: Check if secret is protected from deletion
        If secret.metadata.metadata contains "deletion_protected" and secret.metadata.metadata["deletion_protected"] and not final_force:
            Return SecretException with:
                error_message as "Secret is protected from deletion. Use force=true to override."
                error_code as "DELETION_PROTECTED"
        
        Note: Perform soft delete (mark as deleted) or hard delete based on configuration
        Let deletion_type be If final_store.store_config contains "soft_delete" and final_store.store_config["soft_delete"] then "soft" else "hard"
        
        Let deletion_result be Match deletion_type:
            When "soft":
                soft_delete_secret_from_backend with:
                    secret_id as secret_id
                    store as final_store
            Otherwise:
                hard_delete_secret_from_backend with:
                    secret_id as secret_id
                    store as final_store
        
        If not deletion_result.success:
            Return SecretException with:
                error_message as "Secret deletion failed: " plus deletion_result.error_message
                error_code as "DELETION_ERROR"
        
        Note: Revoke all access permissions for this secret
        Let revoke_result be revoke_all_secret_access with:
            secret_id as secret_id
            store as final_store
        
        Note: Log audit event
        If secret.metadata.audit_enabled:
            log_audit_event with:
                event_type as "SECRET_DELETED"
                secret_id as secret_id
                principal as get_current_principal
                operation as "delete"
                success as true
                additional_data as dictionary containing:
                    "deletion_type" as deletion_type
                    "secret_name" as secret.metadata.name
                    "force_delete" as final_force
        
        Return SecretSuccess with:
            value as true
            audit_info as dictionary containing:
                "operation" as "delete"
                "secret_id" as secret_id
                "deletion_type" as deletion_type
                "timestamp" as current_time
    
    Catch error:
        log_audit_event with:
            event_type as "SECRET_DELETION_FAILED"
            secret_id as secret_id
            principal as get_current_principal
            operation as "delete"
            success as false
            additional_data as dictionary containing "error" as error.message
        
        Return SecretException with:
            error_message as "Secret deletion exception: " plus error.message
            error_code as "DELETION_EXCEPTION"
:End Note

Note: Secret Rotation and Lifecycle Management
Process called "rotate_secret" that takes secret_id as String and new_value as Optional[String] and rotation_config as Optional[Dictionary[String, Any]] and store as Optional[SecretStore] returns SecretResult[Dictionary[String, Any]]:
    Let current_time be get_current_timestamp
    Let final_store be store if store is not None else get_default_secret_store
    Let final_config be rotation_config if rotation_config is not None else dictionary containing
    
    Try:
        Note: Validate rotation permissions
        Let permission_check be check_secret_permission with:
            principal as get_current_principal
            operation as "rotate"
            resource as secret_id
            store as final_store
        
        If not permission_check.allowed:
            Return SecretAccessDenied with:
                secret_id as secret_id
                principal as get_current_principal
                required_permission as "rotate"
        
        Note: Retrieve existing secret
        Let retrieve_result be retrieve_secret_from_backend with:
            secret_id as secret_id
            store as final_store
        
        If not retrieve_result.found:
            Return SecretNotFound with:
                secret_id as secret_id
                reason as "Cannot rotate non-existent secret"
        
        Let existing_secret be retrieve_result.secret
        
        Note: Generate new value if not provided
        Let rotation_value be If new_value is not None then new_value else generate_secret_value with:
            secret_type as existing_secret.metadata.secret_type
            config as final_config
        
        Note: Validate new value
        Let validation_result be validate_secret_value with:
            value as rotation_value
            secret_type as existing_secret.metadata.secret_type
        
        If not validation_result.valid:
            Return SecretException with:
                error_message as "Rotation value validation failed: " plus validation_result.error_message
                error_code as "VALIDATION_ERROR"
        
        Note: Archive current version before rotation
        Let archive_result be archive_secret_version with:
            secret as existing_secret
            store as final_store
        
        Note: Update secret with new value
        Let update_result be update_secret with:
            secret_id as secret_id
            new_value as rotation_value
            metadata as dictionary containing "last_rotation" as current_time
            store as final_store
        
        Match update_result:
            When SecretSuccess:
                Note: Notify rotation completion if configured
                If final_config contains "notify_on_rotation" and final_config["notify_on_rotation"]:
                    notify_secret_rotation with:
                        secret_id as secret_id
                        old_version as existing_secret.metadata.version
                        new_version as update_result.value
                        config as final_config
                
                Note: Schedule next rotation if configured
                If existing_secret.metadata.rotation_interval is not None:
                    schedule_next_rotation with:
                        secret_id as secret_id
                        interval as existing_secret.metadata.rotation_interval
                        store as final_store
                
                log_audit_event with:
                    event_type as "SECRET_ROTATED"
                    secret_id as secret_id
                    principal as get_current_principal
                    operation as "rotate"
                    success as true
                    additional_data as dictionary containing:
                        "old_version" as existing_secret.metadata.version
                        "new_version" as update_result.value
                        "rotation_type" as If new_value is not None then "manual" else "automatic"
                
                Return SecretSuccess with:
                    value as dictionary containing:
                        "old_version" as existing_secret.metadata.version
                        "new_version" as update_result.value
                        "rotation_timestamp" as current_time
                        "next_rotation" as If existing_secret.metadata.rotation_interval is not None then current_time plus existing_secret.metadata.rotation_interval else None
                    audit_info as update_result.audit_info
            
            Otherwise:
                Return update_result
    
    Catch error:
        log_audit_event with:
            event_type as "SECRET_ROTATION_FAILED"
            secret_id as secret_id
            principal as get_current_principal
            operation as "rotate"
            success as false
            additional_data as dictionary containing "error" as error.message
        
        Return SecretException with:
            error_message as "Secret rotation exception: " plus error.message
            error_code as "ROTATION_EXCEPTION"

Process called "list_secrets" that takes filters as Optional[Dictionary[String, Any]] and pagination as Optional[Dictionary[String, Any]] and store as Optional[SecretStore] returns SecretResult[List[SecretMetadata]]:
    Let final_store be store if store is not None else get_default_secret_store
    Let final_filters be filters if filters is not None else dictionary containing
    Let final_pagination be pagination if pagination is not None else dictionary containing
    
    Try:
        Note: Validate list permissions
        Let permission_check be check_secret_permission with:
            principal as get_current_principal
            operation as "list"
            resource as "*"
            store as final_store
        
        If not permission_check.allowed:
            Return SecretAccessDenied with:
                secret_id as "*"
                principal as get_current_principal
                required_permission as "list"
        
        Note: Apply default pagination
        Let page_size be get_safe_value with dict as final_pagination and key as "page_size" and default as 50
        Let page_offset be get_safe_value with dict as final_pagination and key as "page_offset" and default as 0
        
        Note: Retrieve secrets list from backend
        Let list_result be list_secrets_from_backend with:
            filters as final_filters
            pagination as final_pagination
            store as final_store
        
        If not list_result.success:
            Return SecretException with:
                error_message as "Secret listing failed: " plus list_result.error_message
                error_code as "LIST_ERROR"
        
        Note: Filter out secrets the user doesn't have access to
        Let accessible_secrets be list containing
        For each secret_metadata in list_result.secrets:
            Let access_check be check_secret_permission with:
                principal as get_current_principal
                operation as "read"
                resource as secret_metadata.secret_id
                store as final_store
            
            If access_check.allowed:
                Add secret_metadata to accessible_secrets
        
        Note: Log audit event
        log_audit_event with:
            event_type as "SECRETS_LISTED"
            secret_id as None
            principal as get_current_principal
            operation as "list"
            success as true
            additional_data as dictionary containing:
                "total_visible" as length of accessible_secrets
                "filters_applied" as final_filters
                "page_size" as page_size
                "page_offset" as page_offset
        
        Return SecretSuccess with:
            value as accessible_secrets
            audit_info as dictionary containing:
                "operation" as "list"
                "total_count" as length of accessible_secrets
                "page_size" as page_size
                "page_offset" as page_offset
    
    Catch error:
        log_audit_event with:
            event_type as "SECRET_LIST_FAILED"
            secret_id as None
            principal as get_current_principal
            operation as "list"
            success as false
            additional_data as dictionary containing "error" as error.message
        
        Return SecretException with:
            error_message as "Secret listing exception: " plus error.message
            error_code as "LIST_EXCEPTION"

Process called "get_secret_metadata" that takes secret_id as String and store as Optional[SecretStore] returns SecretResult[SecretMetadata]:
    Let final_store be store if store is not None else get_default_secret_store
    
    Try:
        Note: Validate metadata access permissions
        Let permission_check be check_secret_permission with:
            principal as get_current_principal
            operation as "metadata"
            resource as secret_id
            store as final_store
        
        If not permission_check.allowed:
            Return SecretAccessDenied with:
                secret_id as secret_id
                principal as get_current_principal
                required_permission as "metadata"
        
        Note: Retrieve secret metadata
        Let metadata_result be get_secret_metadata_from_backend with:
            secret_id as secret_id
            store as final_store
        
        If not metadata_result.found:
            Return SecretNotFound with:
                secret_id as secret_id
                reason as "Secret metadata not found"
        
        log_audit_event with:
            event_type as "SECRET_METADATA_ACCESSED"
            secret_id as secret_id
            principal as get_current_principal
            operation as "metadata"
            success as true
            additional_data as dictionary containing
        
        Return SecretSuccess with:
            value as metadata_result.metadata
            audit_info as dictionary containing:
                "operation" as "metadata"
                "secret_id" as secret_id
    
    Catch error:
        Return SecretException with:
            error_message as "Secret metadata retrieval exception: " plus error.message
            error_code as "METADATA_EXCEPTION"
:End Note

Note: Secret Access Control and Permissions
Process called "grant_secret_access" that takes secret_id as String and principal as String and permissions as List[String] and conditions as Optional[Dictionary[String, Any]] and expires_at as Optional[Float] and store as Optional[SecretStore] returns SecretResult[String]:
    Let current_time be get_current_timestamp
    Let final_store be store if store is not None else get_default_secret_store
    Let final_conditions be conditions if conditions is not None else dictionary containing
    Let access_id be generate_access_id
    
    Try:
        Note: Validate permission to grant access
        Let permission_check be check_secret_permission with:
            principal as get_current_principal
            operation as "grant_access"
            resource as secret_id
            store as final_store
        
        If not permission_check.allowed:
            Return SecretAccessDenied with:
                secret_id as secret_id
                principal as get_current_principal
                required_permission as "grant_access"
        
        Note: Verify secret exists
        Let secret_exists be check_secret_exists with:
            secret_id as secret_id
            store as final_store
        
        If not secret_exists:
            Return SecretNotFound with:
                secret_id as secret_id
                reason as "Cannot grant access to non-existent secret"
        
        Note: Validate permissions list
        Let valid_permissions be list containing "read", "update", "delete", "rotate", "grant_access", "revoke_access", "metadata"
        For each permission in permissions:
            If not valid_permissions contains permission:
                Return SecretException with:
                    error_message as "Invalid permission: " plus permission
                    error_code as "INVALID_PERMISSION"
        
        Note: Create access grant
        Let secret_access be SecretAccess with:
            access_id as access_id
            secret_id as secret_id
            principal as principal
            permissions as permissions
            granted_by as get_current_principal
            granted_at as current_time
            expires_at as expires_at
            conditions as final_conditions
            audit_trail as list containing
            metadata as dictionary containing
        
        Note: Store access grant
        Let store_access_result be store_secret_access with:
            access as secret_access
            store as final_store
        
        If not store_access_result.success:
            Return SecretException with:
                error_message as "Failed to store access grant: " plus store_access_result.error_message
                error_code as "ACCESS_STORAGE_ERROR"
        
        log_audit_event with:
            event_type as "SECRET_ACCESS_GRANTED"
            secret_id as secret_id
            principal as get_current_principal
            operation as "grant_access"
            success as true
            additional_data as dictionary containing:
                "granted_to" as principal
                "permissions" as permissions
                "access_id" as access_id
                "expires_at" as expires_at
        
        Return SecretSuccess with:
            value as access_id
            audit_info as dictionary containing:
                "operation" as "grant_access"
                "access_id" as access_id
                "granted_to" as principal
                "permissions" as permissions
    
    Catch error:
        Return SecretException with:
            error_message as "Access grant exception: " plus error.message
            error_code as "GRANT_ACCESS_EXCEPTION"

Process called "revoke_secret_access" that takes access_id as String and store as Optional[SecretStore] returns SecretResult[Boolean]:
    Let current_time be get_current_timestamp
    Let final_store be store if store is not None else get_default_secret_store
    
    Try:
        Note: Retrieve access grant details
        Let access_result be get_secret_access_details with:
            access_id as access_id
            store as final_store
        
        If not access_result.found:
            Return SecretNotFound with:
                secret_id as "unknown"
                reason as "Access grant not found"
        
        Let access_grant be access_result.access
        
        Note: Validate permission to revoke access
        Let permission_check be check_secret_permission with:
            principal as get_current_principal
            operation as "revoke_access"
            resource as access_grant.secret_id
            store as final_store
        
        If not permission_check.allowed:
            Return SecretAccessDenied with:
                secret_id as access_grant.secret_id
                principal as get_current_principal
                required_permission as "revoke_access"
        
        Note: Revoke access
        Let revoke_result be revoke_secret_access_from_backend with:
            access_id as access_id
            store as final_store
        
        If not revoke_result.success:
            Return SecretException with:
                error_message as "Failed to revoke access: " plus revoke_result.error_message
                error_code as "ACCESS_REVOKE_ERROR"
        
        log_audit_event with:
            event_type as "SECRET_ACCESS_REVOKED"
            secret_id as access_grant.secret_id
            principal as get_current_principal
            operation as "revoke_access"
            success as true
            additional_data as dictionary containing:
                "revoked_from" as access_grant.principal
                "access_id" as access_id
                "original_permissions" as access_grant.permissions
        
        Return SecretSuccess with:
            value as true
            audit_info as dictionary containing:
                "operation" as "revoke_access"
                "access_id" as access_id
                "revoked_from" as access_grant.principal
    
    Catch error:
        Return SecretException with:
            error_message as "Access revocation exception: " plus error.message
            error_code as "REVOKE_ACCESS_EXCEPTION"

Process called "check_secret_permission" that takes principal as String and operation as String and resource as String and store as SecretStore returns Dictionary[String, Any]:
    Try:
        Note: Check if principal has admin privileges
        If is_admin_principal with principal as principal:
            Return dictionary containing:
                "allowed" as true
                "reason" as "admin_privileges"
                "effective_permissions" as list containing "all"
        
        Note: Get all access grants for this principal and resource
        Let access_grants be get_principal_access_grants with:
            principal as principal
            secret_id as resource
            store as store
        
        Note: Check each access grant
        For each access_grant in access_grants:
            Note: Check if access has expired
            If access_grant.expires_at is not None and get_current_timestamp is greater than access_grant.expires_at:
                Continue
            
            Note: Check conditions if any
            If length of access_grant.conditions is greater than 0:
                Let condition_check be evaluate_access_conditions with:
                    conditions as access_grant.conditions
                    context as get_current_access_context
                
                If not condition_check.satisfied:
                    Continue
            
            Note: Check if this grant includes the required permission
            If access_grant.permissions contains operation or access_grant.permissions contains "all":
                Return dictionary containing:
                    "allowed" as true
                    "reason" as "explicit_grant"
                    "access_id" as access_grant.access_id
                    "effective_permissions" as access_grant.permissions
        
        Note: Check store-level policies
        Let policy_check be check_store_access_policy with:
            principal as principal
            operation as operation
            resource as resource
            store as store
        
        If policy_check.allowed:
            Return policy_check
        
        Note: No access found
        Return dictionary containing:
            "allowed" as false
            "reason" as "no_access_grants"
            "effective_permissions" as list containing
    
    Catch error:
        Return dictionary containing:
            "allowed" as false
            "reason" as "permission_check_error"
            "error" as error.message
            "effective_permissions" as list containing
:End Note

Note: Secret Encryption and Security Operations
Process called "encrypt_secret_value" that takes value as String and config as Dictionary[String, Any] and store as SecretStore returns Dictionary[String, Any]:
    Try:
        Let encryption_config be get_encryption_config_from_store with store as store
        
        Note: Generate encryption components
        Let key_result be derive_encryption_key with:
            master_key_id as store.master_key_id
            context as dictionary containing "secret_encryption" as true
            config as encryption_config
        
        If not key_result.success:
            Return dictionary containing:
                "success" as false
                "error_message" as "Key derivation failed: " plus key_result.error_message
        
        Let iv be generate_secure_random_bytes with size as encryption_config.iv_size
        Let salt be generate_secure_random_bytes with size as encryption_config.salt_size
        
        Note: Compress value if enabled
        Let processed_value be If encryption_config.compression_enabled then compress_data with data as value else value
        
        Note: Encrypt the value
        Let encryption_result be perform_encryption with:
            plaintext as processed_value
            key as key_result.key
            iv as iv
            algorithm as encryption_config.algorithm
        
        If not encryption_result.success:
            Return dictionary containing:
                "success" as false
                "error_message" as "Encryption failed: " plus encryption_result.error_message
        
        Note: Calculate integrity checksum
        Let checksum be calculate_integrity_checksum with:
            data as encryption_result.ciphertext
            key as key_result.key
        
        Note: Encode for storage
        Let encoded_ciphertext be encode_data with:
            data as encryption_result.ciphertext
            encoding as encryption_config.encoding
        
        Let encoded_iv be encode_data with:
            data as iv
            encoding as encryption_config.encoding
        
        Let encoded_auth_tag be If encryption_result.auth_tag is not None then encode_data with:
            data as encryption_result.auth_tag
            encoding as encryption_config.encoding
        else None
        
        Return dictionary containing:
            "success" as true
            "encrypted_data" as encoded_ciphertext
            "algorithm" as encryption_config.algorithm
            "key_id" as key_result.key_id
            "iv" as encoded_iv
            "auth_tag" as encoded_auth_tag
            "compressed" as encryption_config.compression_enabled
            "encoding" as encryption_config.encoding
            "checksum" as checksum
            "error_message" as ""
    
    Catch error:
        Return dictionary containing:
            "success" as false
            "error_message" as "Encryption exception: " plus error.message

Process called "decrypt_secret_value" that takes encrypted_data as String and encryption_algorithm as String and key_id as String and iv as String and auth_tag as Optional[String] and config as Dictionary[String, Any] and store as SecretStore returns Dictionary[String, Any]:
    Try:
        Note: Retrieve decryption key
        Let key_result be derive_encryption_key with:
            master_key_id as key_id
            context as dictionary containing "secret_decryption" as true
            config as get_encryption_config_from_store with store as store
        
        If not key_result.success:
            Return dictionary containing:
                "success" as false
                "error_message" as "Key derivation failed: " plus key_result.error_message
        
        Note: Decode from storage format
        Let encryption_config be get_encryption_config_from_store with store as store
        Let decoded_ciphertext be decode_data with:
            data as encrypted_data
            encoding as encryption_config.encoding
        
        Let decoded_iv be decode_data with:
            data as iv
            encoding as encryption_config.encoding
        
        Let decoded_auth_tag be If auth_tag is not None then decode_data with:
            data as auth_tag
            encoding as encryption_config.encoding
        else None
        
        Note: Decrypt the value
        Let decryption_result be perform_decryption with:
            ciphertext as decoded_ciphertext
            key as key_result.key
            iv as decoded_iv
            auth_tag as decoded_auth_tag
            algorithm as encryption_algorithm
        
        If not decryption_result.success:
            Return dictionary containing:
                "success" as false
                "error_message" as "Decryption failed: " plus decryption_result.error_message
        
        Note: Decompress if needed
        Let final_value be If encryption_config.compression_enabled then decompress_data with data as decryption_result.plaintext else decryption_result.plaintext
        
        Return dictionary containing:
            "success" as true
            "decrypted_value" as final_value
            "error_message" as ""
    
    Catch error:
        Return dictionary containing:
            "success" as false
            "error_message" as "Decryption exception: " plus error.message
:End Note

Note: Utility and Helper Functions
Process called "generate_secret_id" returns String:
    Let timestamp be get_current_timestamp
    Let random_component be generate_secure_random_string with length as 16
    Return "secret_" plus timestamp as String plus "_" plus random_component

Process called "generate_access_id" returns String:
    Let timestamp be get_current_timestamp
    Let random_component be generate_secure_random_string with length as 12
    Return "access_" plus timestamp as String plus "_" plus random_component

Process called "get_current_principal" returns String:
    Note: Implementation should return current authenticated principal/user
    Return "system"

Process called "get_current_timestamp" returns Float:
    Note: Returns current system timestamp with microsecond precision
    Let time_result be system_call_current_time
    Return time_result.seconds as Float plus (time_result.microseconds as Float divided by 1000000.0)

Process called "get_safe_value" that takes dict as Dictionary[String, Any] and key as String and default as Any returns Any:
    If dict contains key:
        Return dict[key]
    Otherwise:
        Return default

Process called "validate_secret_value" that takes value as String and secret_type as SecretType returns Dictionary[String, Any]:
    Note: Validate secret value based on type
    Return dictionary containing "valid" as true, "error_message" as ""

Process called "generate_secret_value" that takes secret_type as SecretType and config as Dictionary[String, Any] returns String:
    Note: Generate appropriate secret value for type
    Return "generated_secret_value"

Process called "get_default_secret_store" returns SecretStore:
    Note: Get default secret store configuration
    Return SecretStore with:
        store_id as "default"
        store_type as "file"
        store_config as dictionary containing
        encryption_enabled as true
        master_key_id as "default_master_key"
        access_policy as dictionary containing
        audit_config as dictionary containing
        performance_metrics as dictionary containing
        created_at as get_current_timestamp
        last_health_check as None
        metadata as dictionary containing

Process called "log_audit_event" that takes event_type as String and secret_id as Optional[String] and principal as String and operation as String and success as Boolean and additional_data as Dictionary[String, Any] returns None:
    Note: Log audit event for security monitoring
    Return None

Process called "generate_secure_random_string" that takes length as Integer returns String:
    Note: Generate cryptographically secure random string
    Return "secure_random_string"

Process called "generate_secure_random_bytes" that takes size as Integer returns String:
    Note: Generate cryptographically secure random bytes
    Return "secure_random_bytes"
:End Note

